There’s no way that I can be typing this but I am…. Our son, Dorian Zev Kweller, was killed last night. He was only 16 and he was a true legend. Kindest, gentle soul, a friend to all. If you knew him, you know. We’ll never get over him as long as we’re here on earth. Please keep his spirit alive with your memories and the music he made: @reallyzev. Dorian Zev wrote and recorded songs every day. A true poet from the day he started speaking. Only a few of his recordings were released but he was on a path and excited about his journey. He had so many plans!!! His first gig was in two weeks, at SXSW. My last text with him was about the merch he wanted to make. My baby boy was at the starting line with so much life ahead of him… I have no idea why things like this happen. We’re in complete shock and don’t know what the future holds. Lizzy, Judah, and I have no idea how to deal with this disaster. Thank you for your prayers and support and we apologize if we are slow to respond to messages. 💔
We lay our baby boy to rest on Friday. We’ve set up the Dorian Zev Kweller Memorial fund which is going to do great things. Please consider making a donation. Link in bio. 💔

“Dress like your parent day” (age 11) Dorian used that same LL Bean backpack school-year after school-year. He’d graffitied on it so many times that it became its own unique relic of art ✨ At Dorian’s funeral on Friday, a teenager walked up to me. She said, “Mr. Kweller, I wanted to let you know that I recently moved to Dripping Springs and Dorian was the first person I met. He was so caring and wanted me to have the best experience possible. In between classes, I looked for his green backpack floating through the crowd. Once I spotted it I’d run over to walk with him because he made me feel so at home in my new school.” #friendtoall #doriankweller #dorianzevkweller #helpothers #beauthentic #gonetoosoon
Thank you. Just, thank you. 😭

Today was supposed to be a joyous day. I’ve been looking forward to this release for over a year now. It feels wrong writing anything, but like I said in my last post, I need to push through. There’s so much in these 33 songs… The core album was recorded with inspiration and many laughs alongside dear friends @johndavidkent @joshlattanzi @stephen_harris_music @kimyadawson and Steve Mazur. The 22 rarities and B-sides are straight from the archives. You’ll recognize a few from the Limewire/Napster days + some great duets with @grif1111 @evangriffithdando @thelemonheadsofficial @nilslofgrenofficial @julianahatfield and Dorian’s godfather @averagecabbage. This release is a celebration of a magical time in New York City 20 years ago. Sha Sha Deluxe is available on DSPs and at your favorite record shops worldwide. It’s also available on benkweller.com. I hope that listening to this collection brings you as much joy as assembling it brought to me. ✨❤️

I’ve cleared everything off my schedule except these two events that are deeply personal to me. Thursday at Waterloo was going to be a performance and signing. I’m only going to do the signing now. I’d love to see any of you who want to stop by and say hello. Friday is the official NoiseCo showcase that has been in the works for months. Special shout-out to the NoiseCo staff for working their assets off and continuing to persevere under these circumstances. ❤️ ZEV was going to open the evening with his debut live performance. Now we will open the evening with a video tribute featuring footage that his friends have put together set to his rad music. As for me, I’m committed to try and perform for you all, and for him. All other NoiseCo artists will perform as planned. $20 admission for those who don’t have wristbands. A portion of the proceeds will go to the Zev Foundation. ❤️ you all.

Tonight we play Paper Tiger in San Antonio. My first show in SA was right here in this very room. Back then it was called the White Rabbit. I was a teenager fronting the band Radish. The last time I played here was on June 5th, 2015. Dorian was 8 and Judah was 5. As usual, we jammed at soundcheck - Judah on drums, Dorian on guitar. They sold the merch and it was a family affair. Tonight would’ve been Dorian’s first show in SA as @reallyzev. Even though he isn’t with us physically, his music and spirit fill up the room. please stop by if you’re in the area. Today I’m releasing a cover of Adam Green’s “Her Father and Her”. It’s one of my favorite songs by one of my favorite artists. Adam and I met in the lower east side at the turn of the century and we became instant brothers. He was by my side and in the trenches with me for many shared milestones back in NYC. He’s a close confidante to Lizzy and me and was a huge source of inspiration to his godson, Dorian. 💔 I hope this version shines a new light on his classic anti-folk jam and I hope it opens up a new audience to the brilliant writing of m’dude, AG. ❌🅾️ BK

2023 Poster revealed! 🚨 As tradition has it, every November we drop a special poster that represents the previous year. It’s no secret that 2023 has been the hardest year of my life. I lost my beloved son, Dorian Zev, in a freak-fluke car accident. Although he isn't with us physically, his spirit and music lives on…. 🐺✨This poster is an ode to the loyal wolf that he was. Designed by Austin art legend, Mishka Westell, who watched Dorian grow up over the years. 🐺✨ Printed by past poster collaborator, Dan Grissom. ORDER NOW while supplies last and don’t forget, if you are a “Life member”, you will get this poster for FREE. Learn more about that at benkweller.com 💀🍓
